channel.title: SYI Nulling
channel.description:
Everyone here should know what the Syipkpker does. It has two options: sending fake login packets and nulling. In order for my friend to be able to stop both of them, he needs to know what exactly "nulling" does. Anyone here know?
Oh, and he said that limiting connections per IP should help. But I figured I'd ask here anyways.

What the fuck? I come here asking a simple question and then I get flamed by some jackass (“Or if certain people weren’t complete fucking arrogant morons”) and you are going to remove me from the community? I understand it’s in the wrong section, and as I have fucking posted before I made a new fucking thread.

One question, one answer. If it’s a simple answer, then why is it so hard for anyone to just post it? Seriously, just someone post the answer. This is pretty BS that a fucking member has to go through this just for a yes or no answer and a simple explanation. (Notice how I am not requesting a full fucking tutorial in Java on how to prevent it, I am just asking what it is and if an IP ban would work.)

So “yes”, it works, or “no”, it requires another method. Honestly, it should be easier to put that than redirecting someone to a different forum…[/quote]
